[SN]TITLE[SN]
BBC wins radio rights to broadcast 144 Premier League games per season

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
The BBC has won radio rights to broadcast live Premier League games for the next three seasons.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The number of matches broadcast each season will rise from 128 to 144.
This includes the early Saturday kick-off, the first pick of the 15:00 BST kick-offs, Sunday, Monday, midweek and Friday matches until 2019.
BBC Director of Sport Barbara Slater said: "Live radio coverage is a critical element of the BBC's overall audience offer for football fans."
